                                             <p> 
                                                Dr. Maheswar Rupakheti is a climate scientist and research group leader at the Research Institute for Sustainability (RIFS) | at GFZ Helmholtz Centre for Geosciences in Potsdam, Germany. He leads the "Regional Air Quality and Climate in Southern Asia" group. He also serves as a Vice-Chair of Working Group I of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) - the first Nepali scientist elected in the IPCC Bureau. With 27+ years of research and science-policy experience, his work focuses on air quality and climate change in the Himalayan region and South Asia. He also serves on the steering committees of the International Commission on Atmospheric Chemistry and Global Pollution (ICACGP) and the Atmospheric Composition and the Asian Monsoon (ACAM). He holds a PhD in atmospheric science (Dalhousie University, Canada), an MSc in environmental engineering and management (AIT, Thailand), and an MSc in Physics (Tribhuvan University, Nepal). 
                                                With over 100 research publications, he is ranked among the world‚Äôs top 2% researchers (ScholarGPS, 2024 and 2025).    
                                            </p>
                                            <br>
